original_title: Brooklyn: Elliott Place N. - Auburn Place
text:
North Elliott Place, at Auburn Place. View 1 is north on the former toward Park Avenue from No 91. View 2 shows the west side of the street where demolition took place from the Fort Greene Houses. Public School No. 67 and the Public Library (left) are seen. View 3 is east on Auburn Place.

P. L. Sperr

View 1,2: 1939
View 3: 1941

original_title: Brooklyn: Elliott Place N. - Auburn Place
text:
North Elliott Place, north from Auburn Place. On the right is a portion of the New Cumberland Hospital; in the background, the U. S. Navy Yard; and on the left Public School No. 67.

View 1: September 6, 1939
Views 2, 3: August 23, 1939

P. L. Sperr

Note: Buildings on the west side of the street were razed for the erection of Four Greene Houses.
